The paper deals with decoding of polar codes over channels with intersymbol interference (ISI), which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and communication theory (cs.COMM). The proposed decoding algorithm involves recursion formulas and trellis decoding, which are techniques commonly used in digital signal processing (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the performance improvement achieved by the proposed algorithm, which is a topic related to system identification (cs.SI) and network information theory (cs.NI).
